Sentencas: Iron-cobalt-based perovskite oxides with general formula Ln(0.7)Sr(0.3)Fe(0.8)Co(0.2)O(3-delta) (where Ln = La, Pr and Gd) have been investigated for their application as intermediate-temperature cathodes in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes

Sentencas: Powdered samples of these materials were synthesized by a novel gel combustion process and then characterized by X-ray powder diffraction (XPD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes

Sentencas: XPD patterns were satisfactorily indexed with an orthorhombic GdFeO3-type structure and, for all samples, a mean particle size of less than 1 mu m was estimated from the SEM data.
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes

Sentencas: Experimental single-chamber SOFCs using with these materials as cathodes and NiO-SDC (samaria-doped ceria) and SDC as anode and electrolyte, respectively, were evaluated at 600 degrees C in a methane/oxygen mixtures.
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes

Sentencas: Peak power densities of 65.4, 48.7 and 46.2 mW cm(-2) were obtained for Ag vertical bar Ln(0.7)Sr(0.3)Fe(0.8)Co(0.2)O(3-delta)vertical bar SDC vertical bar NiO-SDC vertical bar Pt cells with Ln = Pr, La and Gd, respectively.
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes

Sentencas: The relatively high power density obtained for the Pr compound shows that it could be an interesting material for cathode of single-chamber SOFCs.
Titulo: Development of electrolyte-supported intermediate-temperature single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells using Ln0.7Sr0.3Fe0.8Co0.2O3-δ (Ln = Pr, La, Gd) cathodes
